{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":801,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":4720,"text":"Roughly 43,000 years ago,"},{"time":7440,"text":"a young cave bear\ndied in the rolling hills"},{"time":10440,"text":"on the northwest border\nof modern day Slovenia."},{"time":13840,"text":"A thousand years later,\na mammoth died in southern Germany."},{"time":17960,"text":"A few centuries after that,\na griffon vulture also died"},{"time":21280,"text":"in the same vicinity."},{"time":23280,"text":"And we know almost nothing\nabout how these animals met their deaths,"},{"time":27440,"text":"but these different creatures\ndispersed across both time and space"},{"time":31520,"text":"did share one remarkable fate."},{"time":34720,"text":"After their deaths,\na bone from each of their skeletons"},{"time":38200,"text":"was crafted by human hands"},{"time":40920,"text":"into a flute."}]},{"cues":[{"time":42920,"text":"Think about that for a second."},{"time":44400,"text":"Imagine you're a caveman,\n40,000 years ago."},{"time":47080,"text":"You've mastered fire."},{"time":48760,"text":"You've built simple tools for hunting."},{"time":50840,"text":"You've learned how to craft\ngarments from animal skins"},{"time":53480,"text":"to keep yourself warm in the winter."},{"time":55560,"text":"What would you choose to invent next?"},{"time":58320,"text":"It seems preposterous\nthat you would invent the flute,"},{"time":61480,"text":"a tool that created\nuseless vibrations in air molecules."},{"time":65319,"text":"But that is exactly\nwhat our ancestors did."}]},{"cues":[{"time":69200,"text":"Now this turns out\nto be surprisingly common"},{"time":72640,"text":"in the history of innovation."},{"time":74280,"text":"Sometimes people invent things"},{"time":76240,"text":"because they want to stay alive\nor feed their children"},{"time":79200,"text":"or conquer the village next door."},{"time":81360,"text":"But just as often,"},{"time":82800,"text":"new ideas come into the world"},{"time":84720,"text":"simply because they're fun."},{"time":87520,"text":"And here's the really strange thing:"},{"time":89960,"text":"many of those playful\nbut seemingly frivolous inventions"},{"time":93240,"text":"ended up sparking\nmomentous transformations"},{"time":95880,"text":"in science, in politics and society."}]},{"cues":[{"time":99000,"text":"Take what may be the most\nimportant invention of modern times:"},{"time":102960,"text":"programmable computers."},{"time":104720,"text":"Now, the standard story is that computers\ndescend from military technology,"},{"time":109360,"text":"since many of the early computers\nwere designed specifically"},{"time":112240,"text":"to crack wartime codes\nor calculate rocket trajectories."},{"time":115720,"text":"But in fact, the origins\nof the modern computer"},{"time":119240,"text":"are much more playful,"},{"time":120920,"text":"even musical,"},{"time":122240,"text":"than you might imagine."},{"time":123520,"text":"The idea behind the flute,"},{"time":124800,"text":"of just pushing air through tubes\nto make a sound,"},{"time":127920,"text":"was eventually modified\nto create the first organ"},{"time":130840,"text":"more than 2,000 years ago."},{"time":132600,"text":"Someone came up with the brilliant idea\nof triggering sounds"},{"time":135920,"text":"by pressing small levers with our fingers,"},{"time":138840,"text":"inventing the first musical keyboard."},{"time":141240,"text":"Now, keyboards evolved\nfrom organs to clavichords to harpsichords"},{"time":145400,"text":"to the piano,"},{"time":146760,"text":"until the middle of the 19th century,"},{"time":149440,"text":"when a bunch of inventors\nfinally hit on the idea"},{"time":152240,"text":"of using a keyboard\nto trigger not sounds but letters."},{"time":156160,"text":"In fact, the very first typewriter"},{"time":158480,"text":"was originally called\n\"the writing harpsichord.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":163440,"text":"Flutes and music led\nto even more powerful breakthroughs."},{"time":167280,"text":"About a thousand years ago,"},{"time":169040,"text":"at the height of the Islamic Renaissance,"},{"time":171280,"text":"three brothers in Baghdad\ndesigned a device"},{"time":173640,"text":"that was an automated organ."},{"time":176160,"text":"They called it \"the instrument\nthat plays itself.\""},{"time":179960,"text":"Now, the instrument\nwas basically a giant music box."},{"time":183120,"text":"The organ could be trained to play\nvarious songs by using instructions"},{"time":187480,"text":"encoded by placing pins\non a rotating cylinder."},{"time":191440,"text":"And if you wanted the machine\nto play a different song,"},{"time":194080,"text":"you just swapped a new cylinder in\nwith a different code on it."},{"time":197840,"text":"This instrument was the first of its kind."},{"time":201240,"text":"It was programmable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203000,"text":"Now, conceptually,\nthis was a massive leap forward."},{"time":206080,"text":"The whole idea of hardware and software"},{"time":209520,"text":"becomes thinkable for the first time\nwith this invention."},{"time":212760,"text":"And that incredibly powerful concept"},{"time":215240,"text":"didn't come to us as an instrument\nof war or of conquest,"},{"time":218440,"text":"or necessity at all."},{"time":220160,"text":"It came from the strange delight\nof watching a machine play music."}]},{"cues":[{"time":225320,"text":"In fact, the idea of programmable machines"},{"time":228560,"text":"was exclusively kept alive by music\nfor about 700 years."},{"time":233240,"text":"In the 1700s, music-making machines"},{"time":235760,"text":"became the playthings\nof the Parisian elite."},{"time":239360,"text":"Showmen used the same coded cylinders"},{"time":242560,"text":"to control the physical movements\nof what were called automata,"},{"time":246520,"text":"an early kind of robot."},{"time":248560,"text":"One of the most famous of those robots"},{"time":250520,"text":"was, you guessed it,\nan automated flute player"},{"time":253920,"text":"designed by a brilliant French inventor"},{"time":255840,"text":"named Jacques de Vaucanson."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258279,"text":"And as de Vaucanson\nwas designing his robot musician,"},{"time":261800,"text":"he had another idea."},{"time":263760,"text":"If you could program a machine\nto make pleasing sounds,"},{"time":267760,"text":"why not program it to weave\ndelightful patterns of color out of cloth?"},{"time":272920,"text":"Instead of using the pins of the cylinder\nto represent musical notes,"},{"time":277200,"text":"they would represent\nthreads with different colors."},{"time":280320,"text":"If you wanted a new pattern\nfor your fabric,"},{"time":282840,"text":"you just programmed a new cylinder."},{"time":285200,"text":"This was the first programmable loom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":288560,"text":"Now, the cylinders were too expensive\nand time-consuming to make,"},{"time":292760,"text":"but a half century later,"},{"time":294320,"text":"another French inventor named Jacquard"},{"time":296960,"text":"hit upon the brilliant idea\nof using paper-punched cards"},{"time":301680,"text":"instead of metal cylinders."},{"time":303480,"text":"Paper turned out to be\nmuch cheaper and more flexible"},{"time":306560,"text":"as a way of programming the device."},{"time":308720,"text":"That punch card system inspired\nVictorian inventor Charles Babbage"},{"time":313200,"text":"to create his analytical engine,"},{"time":315720,"text":"the first true programmable computer"},{"time":318360,"text":"ever designed."},{"time":319720,"text":"And punch cards were used\nby computer programmers"},{"time":322440,"text":"as late as the 1970s."}]},{"cues":[{"time":325160,"text":"So ask yourself this question:"},{"time":327800,"text":"what really made\nthe modern computer possible?"},{"time":331320,"text":"Yes, the military involvement\nis an important part of the story,"},{"time":335360,"text":"but inventing a computer\nalso required other building blocks:"},{"time":339120,"text":"music boxes,"},{"time":340360,"text":"toy robot flute players,"},{"time":342400,"text":"harpsichord keyboards,"},{"time":343920,"text":"colorful patterns woven into fabric,"},{"time":346520,"text":"and that's just a small part of the story."},{"time":349360,"text":"There's a long list of world-changing\nideas and technologies"},{"time":352360,"text":"that came out of play:"},{"time":354080,"text":"public museums, rubber,"},{"time":356080,"text":"probability theory, the insurance business"},{"time":358440,"text":"and many more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":359680,"text":"Necessity isn't always\nthe mother of invention."},{"time":363080,"text":"The playful state of mind\nis fundamentally exploratory,"},{"time":367280,"text":"seeking out new possibilities\nin the world around us."},{"time":370920,"text":"And that seeking\nis why so many experiences"},{"time":374440,"text":"that started with simple\ndelight and amusement"},{"time":377480,"text":"eventually led us\nto profound breakthroughs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":381040,"text":"Now, I think this has implications\nfor how we teach kids in school"},{"time":385280,"text":"and how we encourage innovation\nin our workspaces,"},{"time":388520,"text":"but thinking about play\nand delight this way"},{"time":391600,"text":"also helps us detect what's coming next."},{"time":395160,"text":"Think about it: if you were\nsitting there in 1750"},{"time":397560,"text":"trying to figure out\nthe big changes coming to society"},{"time":401120,"text":"in the 19th, the 20th centuries,"},{"time":403040,"text":"automated machines, computers,"},{"time":405120,"text":"artificial intelligence,"},{"time":407080,"text":"a programmable flute"},{"time":408920,"text":"entertaining the Parisian elite"},{"time":411120,"text":"would have been as powerful a clue\nas anything else at the time."},{"time":415840,"text":"It seemed like an amusement at best,"},{"time":418400,"text":"not useful in any serious way,"},{"time":421160,"text":"but it turned out to be\nthe beginning of a tech revolution"},{"time":425040,"text":"that would change the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":426920,"text":"You'll find the future"},{"time":428800,"text":"wherever people are having the most fun."}]}]}